org.commonvox.hbase_column_manager

Class ChangeEventMonitor

  • Object
    • ChangeEventMonitor

  • public class ChangeEventMonitor
extends Object
    A ChangeEventMonitor (obtained via a RepositoryAdmin's getChangeEventMonitor method) provides various get methods by which lists of ChangeEvents may be obtained (grouped and ordered in various ways), and the class provides a static convenience method for outputting a list of ChangeEvents to a CSV file.
    Author:
    Daniel Vimont

      • getAllChangeEventsByUserName

        public List<ChangeEvent> getAllChangeEventsByUserName()
        Get a list of all ChangeEvents in the ColumnManager repository, ordered by user name (as designated by the Java "user.name" property in effect within a session as a change was made).
        Returns:
        complete list of ChangeEvents in user-name and timestamp order

      • getChangeEventsForUserName

        public List<ChangeEvent> getChangeEventsForUserName(String userName)
        Get the ChangeEvents pertaining to a specific user name (as designated by the Java "user.name" property in effect within a session as a change was made), in timestamp order.
        Parameters:
        userName - value of Java "user.name" property in effect when change was made
        Returns:
        list of ChangeEvents pertaining to the user name, in timestamp order

      • getChangeEventsForEntity

        public List<ChangeEvent> getChangeEventsForEntity(EntityType entityType,
                                                  byte[] namespaceName,
                                                  byte[] tableName,
                                                  byte[] columnFamily,
                                                  byte[] columnQualifier)
        Get the ChangeEvents pertaining to a specified Entity (e.g., a specific Table), in timestamp order. Note that some parameters will not apply to some EntityTypes (e.g. columnFamily does not apply when entityType is TABLE), in which case nulls may be submitted for inapplicable parameters.
        Parameters:
        entityType - type of Entity for which ChangeEvent list is to be produced
        namespaceName - Name of Namespace which pertains to the Entity
        tableName - Name of Table which pertains to the Entity (if applicable)
        columnFamily - Name of Column Family which pertains to the Entity (if applicable)
        columnQualifier - Column Qualifier which pertains to the Entity (if applicable)
        Returns:
        list of ChangeEvents pertaining to the specified Entity, in timestamp order

      • exportChangeEventListToCsvFile

        public static void exportChangeEventListToCsvFile(List<ChangeEvent> changeEventList,
                                                  String targetPathString,
                                                  String targetFileNameString)
                                           throws IOException
        Export the submitted list of ChangeEvent objects to a comma-separated-value (CSV) file, one line per ChangeEvent, with the first line of the file consisting of column headers.
        Parameters:
        changeEventList - list of ChangeEvent objects returned by one of the "get" methods of the ChangeEventMonitor class.
        targetPathString - path to which target file should be written.
        targetFileNameString - file name to assign to target file.
        Throws:
        IOException - if a remote or network exception occurs
